        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); padding-left: 1rem;">Simple CLI, Universal Access</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            One command to remember, one command to recall. Works everywhere: terminal, scripts, cron jobs, CI/CD pipelines. No configuration needed. Tab completion for bash and zsh.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Or use MCP integration for natural language access from Claude, Cursor, Windsurf, and 17+ AI tools.
          </p>
